Client Side Attacks
-----------------------------------

Server Side Attacks - The server is the target of the attack and the attack 
   originates from a client system.
   
Client Side Attacks - A targets vulnerabilities in the client are attacked
   by a malicious server process or by malicious data coming from the server.
   Ex: Web, email, IM, FTP, Streaming Media

Stateful Firewall - Is concerned with whether or nots its a legitimate TCP 
   connection.

Packet Filtering Firewall - Where is the packets coming from, where are they
   going to and what ports did it come from and what ports are they going to.
   
   